In [18]:
#Create and append boolean column that represents whether an ad contains age targeting
    #Targeting all age ranges is considered False
def age_target_bool(row):
    all_ages = ["18-24, 25-34, 35-44, 45-54, 55-64, ≥65, Unknown age", "18-24, 25-34, 35-44, 45-54, 55-64, ≥65 "]
    value = row['age_targeting']
    return value not in all_ages if pd.notna(value) else False

df['yes_age_target'] = df.apply(age_target_bool, axis=1)

#View value counts to validate new column
df['yes_age_target'].value_counts()
Out[18]:
False    624
True     376
Name: yes_age_target, dtype: int64

In [21]:
#Create and append column that represents whether an ad contains gender targeting
    #Targeting all represented genders is considered False
def gender_target_bool(row):
    all_genders = ["Male, Female, Unknown gender"]
    value = row['gender_targeting']
    return value not in all_genders if pd.notna(value) else False

df['yes_gender_target'] = df.apply(gender_target_bool, axis=1)

#View value counts to validate new column

#Create and append column that represents whether an ad contains geo targeting
def geo_target_bool(row):
    return pd.notna(row['geo_targeting_included']) or pd.notna(row['geo_targeting_excluded'])
df['yes_geo_target'] = df.apply(geo_target_bool, axis=1)

#Create new table representing ad types for top 10 advertisers
top10_ad_type = pd.get_dummies(top10_df, columns=['ad_type'])
top10_ad_type = top10_ad_type.groupby('advertiser_name')[

top10_ad_type.rename(columns={'ad_type_IMAGE':'image', 'ad_type_TEXT':'text', 'ad_type_VIDEO':'video'}, inplace=True)
